	lives back together and start again. This tough love from society benefits
	everyone as criminals return to being a funcitoning clog helping their
	community.

*** Paragraph 3
	Education is another example of a rehabilitation program offered by prisons
	that help criminals. Prison education can give what is stolen from young
	individuals as a result of their disadvantaged environment. Research shows
	that there is a halving of recidivism amongst criminals after these
	education programs. With employment opportunities for criminals after
	release, they can be given a smooth entry into the workplace through
	connections and work unions established by the prison. These programs
	further benefit society by building intergenerational benefits where
	criminals teach their children their experience and ensuring their families
	members are dicincentivised into criminal careers.

*** Paragraph 4
	Although prisons may seem as the perfect solution towards societal peace,
	prisons can break personal connection of the sentenced. By isolating the
	offending individual, their family may fall apart. Old arguments tuck away
	to the end of time may arise. Some families may abondon the criminal which
	could foster "NOTHING-TO-LOSE" mentaility within the criminal causing him to
